#        object implementing the Node fs interface;
#        users can plug in lightning-fs, BrowserFS,
#        in-memory mock, S3-backed, or any custom
#        backend.  Same code works across all
#        backends
#     3. SUPPORTS SHALLOW + PARTIAL CLONE — implements
#            modern git protocol v2 features including
#            shallow cloning + partial clone filters
#            for efficient large-repo handling
#     4. PROMISE-BASED ASYNC API — every operation
#        returns a Promise; composes with await + the
#        broader async/await ecosystem; no callback
#        spaghetti
#     5. NO NATIVE BINDINGS — pure JS, no compilation
#        step; runs anywhere npm runs; trivial to
#        install in CI + Lambda + Docker contexts
